    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-09-07T13:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-09-07T13:55:00-05:00" n="299"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                <head>299. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Consulate General in Georgetown</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d299fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, POL 1 BR GU-US. Secret; Limit Distribution. Repeated to
                        London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-09-07T14:55:00-04:00">September 7, 1963, 2:55 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Re Georgetown’s 103.<note n="2" xml:id="d299fn2">
                        <ref target="#d297">Document 297</ref>.</note> We have considered suggestion
                    reftel for approach to <persName>Jagan</persName> for discussion USBG
                    relationships and have concluded that disadvantages and potential
                    misinterpretations outweigh possible advantages to US.
                        <persName>Jagan</persName>’s alleged concern about deterioration of
                    relations with US seems inconsistent with attacks <gloss target="#t_PPP1"
                        >PPP</gloss> paper has been making on US and President personally in last
                    few weeks and with series of steps resulting in closer links between <gloss
                        target="#t_BG1">BG</gloss> and Cuba. We also inclined doubt there any
                    individual or group among Jagan’s lieutenants that could command sufficient
                    popular support seriously to challenge his control of party.</p>
                <p>We wish to avoid creating any impression, or enabling <gloss target="#t_PPP1"
                        >PPP</gloss> to do so, that there exists real possibility of improving
                    relations between <gloss target="#t_PPP1">PPP</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Accordingly, we plan adhere to guidance set forth <gloss target="#t_DEPTEL1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 88<note n="3" xml:id="d299fn3">Dated September 3.
                        (Department of State, Central Files, POL 19 BR GU/<gloss target="#t_UN1"
                            >UN</gloss>)</note> and keep contacts with <persName>Jagan</persName> at
                    as low level as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
